{
  "stem": "2735.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] our family had a lot of interaction with the Poles, with the [INAUDIBLE], Poles that lived there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as a rule, they used to show a lot of respect to my parents, especially my mother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember at one time came a chief of police, a new man to town.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I and his daughter became very close friends.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She loved poetry.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She was a dreamer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We used to go and talk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She had brothers that were so anti-Semitic, like the worst image of a hooligan that you can imagine.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Those were her brothers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That I remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably the way they talked, the way they behaved.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I just remember the impression that I know they were terribly anti-Semitic, and I used to think that I was scared of them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I used to love [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Janka, ?] that was her name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, it wasn't very popular to have a close friend that's not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I can't even remember how my parents reacted to what happened.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But since he was like a career man, he didn't stay too long there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he left, I think before-- they left before I left.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Another time, I remember when Pilsudski died.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And those I remember are the times of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Pilsudski died.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My girlfriend was wearing, like a sweater that was the color of brick.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And everybody had to wear, at the school, a black band on their arm.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And some guys attacked her because either she dared to wear red when the country is in such-- and we were crying for Pilsudski.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We learned poems.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We were heartbroken when he was-- but that was the attitude which I remember.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
